climbs.name: The Beef Heart
climbs.fa: Bolted only, did not redpoint, LL2 aka Lee Logston

content.description: Granite that climbs like limestone?  It exists!  Though a bit crumbly, this route ascends a generally solid line with a granite stalactite, positive pockets, crimps, and edges over 4 bolts.  Power down low, techy finish.
content.location: Far right side of the wall.

content.description: This is the set of large rusted chains on the far left of the wall. No bolts or pro; TR only. Not sure if this is an abandoned project. The start is quite hard overhanging slightly with no good feet. There is a large ledge a little over halfway up.
content.protection: TR only; walk around left to set up
content.location: Far left side of the Lunar Wall

content.description: Start by climbing large huecos to a reachy roof. Pull over the roof and enter the thinner dihedral and follow it up to the chains.
content.location: Look for the large huecos at the base. Shares a start with Pocket Rocket before ducking right.

content.description: Has a powerful start to attain the dihedral. Once in the corner follow the bolts up the technical corner.
content.location: Far left side of the wall in a right facing corner with the bolts on the right face.

content.description: Don't let the misting of moon rock stray you from this celestial body. Yeah, there is some chossy rock, but the route is really fun. There is a great dyno and also a fun mantle to top it off. The route is well protected, and can be stick clipped. Just wear your space hat.

Start up the huecos and generally clip to the left. A small roof provides the crux. The huecos are a bit sandy and the rock sounds hollow in spots but all the clipping stances are solid. It should clean up with more ascents. 5 bolts to anchor chains which are set back a bit from the edge so an extended anchor is recommended for TR.
content.location: Obvious line with large huecos all the way up. You cannot miss this line in the middle of the cliff.

climbs.name: Puss Boy
climbs.fa: Brian Loth and Matt Merton (FFA: Peter Vintoniv)

content.location: This the the face climb 4ft looker's right of the little tree at the top of the cliff and the bolted route immediately left of Pocket Rocket

content.description: Climbs up a shallow left facing dihedral with some interesting crack and face moves. Shares the start with Third Alternative
content.location: Look for some large huecos at the start followed  by a thin crack.

content.description:
A pico satellite, aka a nano satellite, are the smallest satellites used for radio communication. Since you are on the moon, and there is little connection with humanity, I thought I would introduce a "Little Pico" to help service the lunar wall.

Little Pico starts up huge hueco's at about 5.10c then moves into the tiny little holds on less than vertical slab, which goes at about 5.11b.
content.protection: 8 stainless bolts + 2 closed shut hooks! You can now lower off this baby
